==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Acetophenone
<hw>Ac`e*to*phe"none</hw> <pr>(-f⟦emac⟧"n⟦omac⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Acet</ets>ic + <ets>phen</ets>yl + <ets>one</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A crystalline ketone,
<chform>CH3.CO.C6H5</chform>, which may be obtained by the dry
distillation of a mixture of the calcium salts of acetic and benzoic
acids. It is used as a hypnotic under the name of
<altname>hypnone</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acetose</ent>⟦br⟧
